    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Any convex, rounded molding which has a partly cylindrical form; commonly used to refer to Gothic or Romanesque rather than classical forms.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
